<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-06T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-06T13:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/595: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-06T21:00:00+03:00">August 6,
                                    1940—9 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 6—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>976. Exchange of notes extending commercial agreement to August 6, 1941,
                            including notes on Soviet coal, took place at 8 o’clock Moscow time
                            tonight. Details follow in a separate telegram.<note n="71" xml:id="d320fn71">Telegram No. 982, August 7, 11 a.m., from the
                                Chargé in the Soviet Union, <ref target="#pg_458">p.
                                458</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>[For text of the agreement effected by exchange of notes signed
                                August 6, 1940, and effective August 6, 1940, see Department of
                                State Executive Agreement Series No. 179, or 54 Stat. (pt. 2) 2366.
                                For text of press release issued by the Department August 7, see
                                Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, August 10,
                                1940, page 105.]</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>